rly feminist writing, sexology books, newspapers, bestselling love treatises, native ethnology, and historiography. While illuminating the ways in which women used and challenged ideas about love, Suzuki explores the historical and ideological shifts of the period, underscoring the broader connections between gender, modernity, and nationhood.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 23. Jul 2020) 0aJapanese fictionxHistory and criticismx20th century. 0aJapanese fictionxWomen authorsxHistory and criticism. 0aJapanese fictiony20th centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aLove in literaturexJapanxElectronic booksxCriticism, interpretation, etc. 0aLove in literature. 0aWomen in literature. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Asian / Japanese.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUP Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311070420440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978080477295240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780804772952423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780804772952.jpg  a978-3-11-070420-4  SUP Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles